Runaway Bundesliga leaders Bayern Munich have proven that despite all the wealth and excess in football, there are still grounded and caring people involved in the game.

The Champions League returns on Tuesday evening as Bayern face Ukrainian side Shakhtar Donetsk in the last 16 first-leg.

During their visit to the war torn country Pep Guardiola’s side have pledged an incredible offer to pay the medical bills for 30 Ukrainian children injured in the on-going conflict with Russia. 

