The match is supposed to be a home game for the Shakhtar Donetsk but due to the political and security situation in the Ukraine, the match has been moved to Lviv,

The Arena Lviv is a staggering 750 miles from their abandoned Donbass Arena, the glistening monument to the team's success now caught up in a warzone.

The problems facing the Ukrainian people have not gone unnoticed by Bayern Munich after club President Karl Hopfner and CEO Karl-Heinz Rummenigge handed out gifts to children injured in the conflict during a visit to the Communal City Clinic Hospital in Lviv. 

